Kiess is a walled city built on the ruins of fallen Evermeet, along Roc Road west of Midgaard.
Evermeet collapsed over generations from neglect; Kiess was built as its deliberate, defensible replacement.
Layout is a walled rectangle with predictable streets, centralized services, and controlled gates.
Three-power governance divides authority: Compact Temples (sanctuary law, civic rites), Trade Syndics (market and caravan contracts), and Wall Command (gates, patrols, watchtowers).
An Executioner stationed at the Central Prism enforces the common peace code binding all three factions.
The Central Prism is a luminous artifact recovered from Evermeet's civic hall, serving as the city's memorial and administrative center.
Founding charter prohibits sealed warrants from predecessor authorities, enacted after discovering Evermeet had transferred condemned debtors to the Spirebound Conclave.
Visual identity: white civic stone, blue-and-gold banners, prismatic glasswork on canal bridges.
North of the city lies the Forest of Confusion, patrolled by Wall Command via rope-line corridors and bell-posts.
Beyond the forest are the Verdant Depths. East, Roc Road leads to Midgaard.
Kiess survives by organizing risk rather than ignoring it.
